cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.MS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with many-valued logics and proof-theoretic frameworks for them. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as many-valued logics are used in AI for reasoning under uncertainty. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as many-valued logics are used in programming language semantics. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as many-valued logics are used in formal language theory. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the construction of calculi for non-Archimedean many-valued logics.
